FTSE 100 Benchmark Advances; Reckitt Benckiser SABMiller, Unilever Climb

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-25T14:35:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/ftse-100-benchmark-advances-reckitt-benckiser-sabmiller-unilever-climb.html
U.K. stocks advanced, with the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index heading for its biggest weekly gain
since November, as consumer shares rallied.  Reckitt Benckiser Group Plc, the maker of Nurofen
painkillers and Strepsils, rose 3.2 percent after BofA Merrill
Lynch Global Research advised buying the shares. Reckitt,
together with SABMiller Plc and Unilever Plc, led personal-goods
companies higher. African Barrick Gold Ltd., the biggest London-
listed producer of the precious metal, surged 3.2 percent after
saying drill results may add “considerable value” to one of
its projects.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index climbed 0.4 percent to
5,906.09 at 2:33 p.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  